  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.53 sitting just below the massive +24B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher while providing support on dips toward the -16B negative gamma pocket at 6590. The 37.3% GEX surge and wall break detection suggest dealers just absorbed significant hedging flow, likely from a volatile move that triggered rebalancing across these key strikes. Watch 6605 as the primary resistance where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while 6590 becomes the critical support level where dealer buying kicks in if we break lower.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers capping upside and defending downside.",
